# /kig-inject — consolidated context injection

Replaces the old `/kig-pin` + `/kig-inject`. Use this to save reminders / context that KIG prepends to every nudge. Entries form a list; each is individually toggleable; a master switch turns the whole block on/off.

Run the backing script with the user's arguments:

```bash
~/bin/kig-inject-cmd.py "$@"
```

## Subcommands

| Command | Effect |
|---|---|
| `add [--project] [--for MODES] "text"` | Append entry (MODES comma-separated: `all` or subset of `minimal,simple,verbose`; default `all`) |
| `remove [--project] <N>` | Remove entry by 1-indexed position |
| `toggle [--project] <N>` | Flip enabled/disabled without removing |
| `list [--project]` | Show all entries with state and mode tags |
| `show [--project]` | Alias for list |
| `on [--project]` | Master switch on |
| `off [--project]` | Master switch off (entries preserved) |
| `clear [--project]` | Wipe all entries + master off |
| `help` | This text |

## Examples

```
/kig-inject add "working on Rust crate — don't touch Python files"
/kig-inject add --for simple "check logs at /tmp/claude-keepitgoing/"
/kig-inject add --for simple,verbose "don't drop the failing test"
/kig-inject list
/kig-inject toggle 2
/kig-inject off
```

## Scope

- **Default:** global (`~/.claude/kig/inject.json`) — affects every session
- **`--project`:** scoped to current project (`./.kig/inject.json`)
